cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with security attacks on deep neural networks (DNNs) during the inference stage, specifically in the context of autonomous driving and traffic sign detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization algorithms used for generating imperceptible attack images, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of pre-trained DNNs and back-propagation algorithm for generating attack images also suggests the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the practical application of the proposed methodology in an autonomous driving use case, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Systems and Control).
